{
  "stem": "9.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was very capable, but he rather had to have his rest every day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Both of them worked beautifully together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They have established a very successful manufacturing of the outerwear business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Outerwear means coats, suits, jackets, and so on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In my childhood, I remember living in a very small apartment with no running water, with very rough wooden floors in the kitchen, with a wooden-burning stove.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we did have three housekeepers, one cook, and two to perform all the other duties.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We have to remember the water had to be brought in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The wood had to be chopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Fire had to be started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was quite a bit of work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The thing that I remember very, very specifically, I have to emphasize again and again the ingenuity of my mother, the upbringing for the future, because, when I was about eight, nine years old, I was taught everything there was to be done in a household, regardless of all the help.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everybody got a day off, and I had to scrub the floor with my little hand.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was crying, but that didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The doors were locked, and I couldn't come out until it was finished.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I remember washing laundry on a scrub board and putting on top of the stove to boil the sheets with my little hands.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then I had to take it out, rinse it, and hang it out outside to dry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I was made to learn-- I was taught how to bake bread with yeast, all kinds of bakeries, how to make dough for the strudel with my hands; how to wash, clean, sew, darn.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "All the socks had to be darned.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I even had to learn how to darn a damask tablecloth.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
